    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in GTPU tunnel release functionality\n\n### Summary\nThe NR CU-UP GTPU tunnel management contained a memory leak when releasing individual tunnels. The bug occurred when `newGtpuDeleteOneTunnel` was called to remove the last remaining tunnel for a UE - the UE entry itself was not being removed from the `ue2te_mapping` hash table, causing the entry to persist indefinitely.\n\nThis issue was particularly noticeable during UE context release procedures where all tunnels for a UE are torn down one by one rather than all at once. Over time, this led to increased memory consumption and potential hash table performance degradation.\n\nThe root cause was inconsistent cleanup logic between `newGtpuDeleteOneTunnel` and the bulk deletion functions `newGtpuDeleteAllTunnels` and `newGtpuDeleteTunnels` which properly handled UE entry removal.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/ocp-gtpu/gtp_itf.cpp`: Added UE entry cleanup in `newGtpuDeleteOneTunnel` when deleting the last bearer for a UE\n- `openair3/ocp-gtpu/gtp_itf.cpp`: Improved logging to handle cases where UE entries are removed\n\n"
}